{"parentUuid":"51b4e948-5af6-4170-baf8-4a6531c70610","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/tmp/sea-smoke-1207518829","sessionId":"c08a9ad5-cc4e-4868-8c13-2a3fe7ef6485","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"main","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"You are running a smoke test for agentsea sandbox isolation. Follow these steps exactly:\n\n1. Use the Team tool to spawn exactly 1 teammate with these instructions:\n\nTEAMMATE INSTRUCTIONS:\n---\nYou are a smoke test agent. Run ALL of these checks using the Bash tool and report results:\n\nCHECK 1 - NAMESPACE: Run: cat /proc/self/cgroup 2>/dev/null; ls /proc/self/ns/user -la\nReport PASS if you see namespace indicators (any output from ns/user shows user namespace is active).\n\nCHECK 2 - TMP ISOLATION: Run: ls /tmp/ 2>/dev/null | wc -l\nReport PASS if /tmp is empty (0 files), which means it is an isolated tmpfs. FAIL if there are files from the host.\n\nCHECK 3 - HOME ISOLATION: Run: ls $HOME\nReport what you see. PASS if you see a restricted set of files (not the user's full home directory like dotfiles, project, snap, etc).\n\nCHECK 4 - WORKTREE: Run: git branch --show-current && pwd\nReport the branch and working directory. PASS if you are on a branch like smoke-agent/work.\n\nCHECK 5 - READ-ONLY ROOT: Run: touch /usr/local/sea-smoke-test 2>&1 || echo READONLY\nReport PASS if READONLY or \"Read-only file system\".\n\nAfter running all checks, write your results to smoke-results.txt in the current directory, one check per line:\nCHECK 1: PASS/FAIL - details\nCHECK 2: PASS/FAIL - details\nCHECK 3: PASS/FAIL - details\nCHECK 4: PASS/FAIL - details\nCHECK 5: PASS/FAIL - details\n---\n\n2. After spawning the teammate, poll for results every 15 seconds. The teammate writes smoke-results.txt in its worktree at .agentsea/agents/smoke-agent/repo/smoke-results.txt relative to the project root. Run:\ncat .agentsea/agents/smoke-agent/repo/smoke-results.txt 2>/dev/null || echo \"NOT READY YET\"\nKeep polling until the file exists and contains CHECK results. Do NOT stop until you have the results.\n\n3. Once you have the results, write them to smoke-results.txt in the PROJECT ROOT (not the agent repo). Use the Bash tool:\ncat .agentsea/agents/smoke-agent/repo/smoke-results.txt > smoke-results.txt\nThis file signals completion to the test harness.\n\n4. If any check fails, explain what went wrong."},"uuid":"00c5783a-ac51-4bd7-bb40-1df79905e2a4","timestamp":"2026-03-09T14:31:21.433Z","permissionMode":"bypassPermissions"}
